SIMPLE: tinkling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tinkling
<hw>Tin"kling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
tinkle, or succession of tinkles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drowsy <qex>tinklings</qex> lull the distant folds.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A grackle (<spn>Quiscalus
crassirostris</spn>) native of Jamaica. It often associates with
domestic cattle, and rids them of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinman</ent>⟦br⟧
